                <h1>Judging a Play: What Criteria Matter?</h1>
                <p>A question that is not a valid criterion for judging a play and its production is, "Did the audience enjoy the snacks?" While audience enjoyment is important, it is unrelated to the artistic and technical elements of the performance itself. Evaluating a play should focus on script quality, acting, direction, and set design rather than refreshments.</p>
